name: Devonian Gardens
description: Indoor botanical gardens including over 500 trees, 50 varieties of plants, a 900 sq. ft. living wall, fountains, fish ponds and a playground to climb and explore.

name: Fish Creek Provincial Park
wheelchair:description: This is the only part of the park where the city bus goes into. Trails are paved, parking is available.

name: Thornhill Aquatic & Recreation Centre
description: swimming pool, hot tub, steam room, weight room; baby sitting available - see webiste

name: Chinook Rotary Nature Park
description: part of Fish Creek Provincial Park, developed by Rotary Chinook (Rotary Club of Calgary); day use area
note: this node exists for location and identification of the park (a named sub-area of Fish Creek Pk) and to acknowledge the contribution of Rotary Chinook
